Brute Force : - O(N^2), O(n)- set space
Approach - I was confused with the length part, i had a solution which stores consecutive elements first and then the length.
But this solution uses two variables res and streak that calculates the len very easily. Set helps in keeping the unique elements,
and the while loop helps in finding the consecutive elements.
The program does the following -
1) Move number by number in the list given
2) Streak set to one for every number at first and curr updated to num
3)While checks for every consecutive number that exists for the number already in list, that too in second iteration
4) At last res max is what adds the length of the consecutive sequence

class Solution:
    def longestConsecutive(self, nums: List[int]) -> int:
        res = 0
        store = set(nums)

        for num in nums:
            streak, curr = 0, num
            while curr in store:
                streak += 1
                curr += 1
            res = max(res,streak)
        return res
        
